-- Responsible Shale Won’t Win Public Over, Chesapeake Says
-- B y   B e n   F a r e y
-- 2012-04-18T17:25:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-18/responsible-shale-won-t-win-public-over-chesapeake-says-1-.html
Responsible exploitation of shale
resources doesn’t ensure winning over public opinion, Mike
Stice, senior vice president at  Chesapeake Energy Corp. (CHK) , told
delegates at the Flame conference in Amsterdam.  U.S. natural-gas prices will rebound as producers reduce
drilling and weather normalizes, Stice said in an interview at
the conference.  To contact the reporter on this story:
